itemDescription: British swimmer, Olympic athlete, British Empire Games gold medallist

wikipedia_page.main: Jack Irwin Hale (8 June 1922 – 29 February 2008) was an English competitive swimmer who represented Great Britain in the Olympic Games and England in the British Empire Games.
